INSERT INTO `wp_rg_lead_detail_long` VALUES (223,'Hello,\r\n\r\nI am looking for a 1br apartment that could be converted into a 2br for July 1st (we are willing to be flexible on move-in date for a great apartment). Would love to get some more information re: size of apartments and ability to flex when you have a minute.\r\n\r\nThank you,\r\n\r\nAlex'),(262,'Hi, my name is Erika Graves and I am very interested in scheduling an appointment to view the 1br apartment. Please feel free to reach me by cell phone. \r\n\r\nI look forward to hearing from you. \r\n\r\nBest,\r\nErika'),(352,'I am interested in renting one of your 1 bedroom apartments and would like to take a look at one of them on the week of May 25. Could you please email/call me about when would be the best time to visit your place? Thank you.'),(365,'Hello,\r\n\r\nI would like to obtain more information about any large 1BRs/Junior 4s you may have - specifically, there is one listed for $4,250 right now on your site. Could you please provide the floorplan? Thank you!\r\n\r\nHeather Boneparth'),(429,'Hi there!\r\nI\'m an Australian student looking for a place to call home in NYC. I would need the apartment from August 1 2015, until February 1 2016. There may be a possibility that I can stay longer, but this will be dependent on my visa. Is this something your residence can provide me with?\r\nIf so, do studio apartments have washers and dryers in the unit?\r\n\r\nBest, \r\nRebekah'),(455,'I saw your availability and was very interested in the apartment. I understand it is currently available and may not be when I am moving but I was hoping you would information potential July availability.'),(527,'The Marketing/Sales Manager,\r\n \r\nWe are planning to visit New York in July/August and inquiring on the availability of a furnished studio/apartment from 4th July to 22nd August.\r\n \r\nI am currently working for Emirates Airlines as Controller Sales and Support and would really appreciate if you could extend Airline/Travel industry discounts for our stay.\r\n \r\nWe are really looking forward to experiencing the hospitality and comfort offered, would appreciate a reply as soon as possible.\r\n \r\nBest Regards,\r\nTasneem Doctor'),(539,'The Marketing/Sales Manager,\r\n \r\nWe are planning to visit New York in July/August and inquiring on the availability of a furnished studio/apartment from 4th July to 22nd August.\r\n \r\nI am currently working for Emirates Airlines as Controller Sales and Support and would really appreciate if you could extend Airline/Travel industry discounts for our stay.\r\n \r\nWe are really looking forward to experiencing the hospitality and comfort offered, would appreciate a reply as soon as possible.\r\n \r\nBest Regards,\r\nTasneem Doctor'),(739,'I\'m interested in the 2 bedroom/2 bathroom that is listed on your website.  Is there a time this week or the first week of June that I can come see it? \r\n\r\nIn the meantime, can you please send me a floorplan of the apartment that is available? \r\n\r\nThanks,\r\nSubir'),(751,'Hello, I was scheduled to move into unit 15J on the night of the 28th. I was curious of what ind of unit I am moving into (Studio/ 1 Bedroom) and also if laundry facilities are available in the building .\r\n\r\nThank You,\r\n\r\nOscar'),(1238,'Hi, I recently saw a studio listed on NY Bits in your building for 2995, Unit #4P. I was wondering whether this studio is still available and if not whether you have similar listings available. Additionally, what is your company policy on walls, pressurized and non-pressurized temporary walls? Feel free to call or email me. Thanks!'),(1294,'Hello,\r\n\r\nMy name is Aavni Piparsania, and I am interested in your 2 bedroom apartments at Monterey at Park. I was wondering if it would be possible to schedule an appointment for  Friday June 5 or Saturday June 6. I am interested in looking for leases that begin in August, and although I realize you may not currently have any apartments available for that time frame, I would like to come by to get a feel for the building and the apartment layouts. Do let me know if that would be possible, I can also give your office a call tomorrow at (646) 396-5459 to check on availability. I can be contacted at piparsaniaa@gmail.com or 215-858-1410. Look forward to hearing from you. \r\n\r\nThank you, \r\nAavni Piparsania'),(1436,'Hello,\r\n\r\nI am looking for a 1 bedroom that can be converted to a 2 bedroom with a temporary wall. Ideally, we would like to move in immediately or by July 01. Please let me know if you have anything that you think we may be interested in.\r\n\r\nThank you,\r\nDan'),(1486,'Hi Monterey Agent,\r\n\r\nI hope this message finds you well. I saw that you have a spacious 1BR apartment available at 30 Park and was wondering if it\'s possible to convert it by putting up a wall. If so, I would be extremely interested in the unit.\r\n\r\nThanks,\r\nDavid'),(1537,'I am looking for an apartment for three people, preferably a flex. We are ideally looking to move in on August 1st but would move in July if the right opportunity presented itself. Please let me know if any of your buildings have openings.'),(1598,'Hi,\r\n\r\nI am very interested in apartment 12E in your building. Specifically, I am looking for a one bed that can be converted to a flex two (have one roommate) and late June move-in date. I would like to schedule a viewing as soon as possible (today or tomorrow). thanks!'),(1669,'Hi,\r\nWhen will you know of your studio availability for late August/ early september?  I want to schedule a visit but want to make sure you know of your availability.  How much are studios generally?  What is included in this price?  Thanks so much.'),(1682,'Hi,\r\nWhen will you know of your studio availability for late August/ early september?  I want to schedule a visit but want to make sure you know of your availability.  How much are studios generally?  What is included in this price?  Thanks so much.'),(1756,'Hi,\r\n\r\nI am looking for a 1 bed with washer/dryer in unit. Do you know if anything will be available for move in Aug or early Sep? What is the price range for a 1 bed with washer/dryer in unit and could you please forward some floor plans?\r\n\r\nThanks!'),(1819,'Interested in seeing unit 4L on Wednesday 6/24.  I am relocating from out of town and am flying out tomorrow at 9pm.  Ideally, seeing the unit at 4:15pm would work well. Let me know what time works from your end.'),(1972,'Hello, \r\nMy clients, Jakob Müllner, and his fiance, Mein Engel, would like to rent a one-bedroom or big studio here. Their budget is around $3000/month. They want to move in by September 1 and rent six months. Can you let me know the rental availabilities? Thank you. \r\nBingo\r\n917-306-6587\r\nbingo.li@corcoran.com'),(2021,'I am looking for a 1 bedroom for October 21 move in date.\r\nPlease let me know if you know of anything coming up. I know we are early but I would still love some basic info on rent, and if we could do a tour to see the building?\r\n\r\nThanks!\r\nStef'),(2033,'Hi,\r\nMy friends and I would like to take a look at any available apartment now to decide whether 30 Park is a place for our move early next year. It\'s highly recommended by a friend of mine so I\'m looking forward to it. Would you let me know if we can take a look at the apartment this coming Sat? Thanks!\r\n\r\nGinger'),(2237,'Good Morning.\r\nI wonder if available studio or a room for annual lease, whether furnished or not, and conditions of the rent (electricity charges, gas, heating and property cooling) and whether there is system (plumbing ready) for washing machine in apartment or just in the building.\r\nThank you for your kindness, Ina'),(2315,'Hi I would like to see the two bedroom that is available at 30 Park today if possible. I am leaving for the airport at about 2pm. I live in Florida. We lived in the building for two years previously.  what is the square footage of the two bedroom apartment?  when is it available? \r\nplease call me at 3057739470 thank you'),(2365,'Hi,\r\n\r\nWe are 2 lawyers, NYU grads, looking for a true 2BR (no flex) in Midtown East/Flatiron. We want to move in on Oct. 1, but a few days earlier should also work. Our budget is $3500, we have no pets.'),(2541,'Hello, \r\nI wanted to apply for a Doorman Position here. I have attached my resume. Thank You\r\nJohnathan M. Pisacone\r\n2023 Lexington Ave #3C New York, NY 10035 (917) 818- 7443 Johnmp2023@aol.com  \r\nObjective	To obtain a position where I can utilize my education and work experience  \r\nSummary of Qualification	Customer Service and Sales Associate\r\nWelcome clients at open house events \r\nAssisted with resolving all customer care needs and disputes\r\nEdit and add photos to backdrop at photo desk \r\nEnsure visual merchandising standards and productivity\r\nAdministrative Intern\r\nGreet caller and forward calls to appropriate departments\r\nResponsible for mail sorting and distribution \r\nHandle general office duties including filing, coping and faxing \r\nFollow up on work performance, customer satisfaction and feedback\r\nMaintenance and Janitorial Service\r\nPerform general cleaning assignments including snow removal\r\nAssisted with preparing and sanitizing worksite to ensure guest safety  \r\nPreparation of residents belonging for storage and moving \r\nStore guest luggage before and after check in and check out\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nSkills    	Construction and Skilled Labor \r\nInstall lighting, receptacles and breaker panels\r\nReplace faulty switches and electrical wires \r\nDisassemble defective electrical equipment\r\n       Cataloging materials for construction projects\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n  \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n 	   \r\n\r\n\r\nProficient In Microsoft applications\r\nExcellent verbal communication \r\nStrong organizational leader	\r\n\r\nAccount receivable \r\nExperience cashier\r\nElectrical Installation \r\n\r\nWork History		\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n	\r\n              \r\n		\r\nDriver	Lumber boys,     New York, NY                                  	 TEMP\r\nDoorperson	70 Park Ave,       New York, NY	 08/2014 - 12/2014\r\n\r\n                                Customer Service Our Cleaners,    New York, NY             10/2010 - 12/2012\r\nEducation \r\n                            Electrical Installation Cooperative Tech, New York, NY     09/2013-01/2014 \r\n		H.S Diploma               Leadership HS, New York, NY         09/2009-06/2013 \r\n			             References are available on');
